Log-Localized
=============

Log::Localized, a module for logging messages based on the
local level of verbosity in the part of the code currently
running, and giving you fine-grained control over the verbosity
level throughout the running code. 

See perldoc Log::Localized for more information.

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

   perl Makefile.PL
   make
   make test
   make install

DEPENDENCIES

This module requires these other modules and libraries:

  Config::Tiny
  Log::Dispatch
  Log::Dispatch::Config
  Log::Dispatch::Screen
  File::Spec
  File::HomeDir

Its tests require additionally:

  Test::NoWarnings
  Test::Warn
  File::Temp
  Test::Pod
  Test::Pod::Coverage 
  Test::Spelling

